						"description": "Returns a sorted list of changes made to documents in the database, in time order of application, can be obtained from the database’s _changes resource. Only the most recent change for a given document is guaranteed to be provided, for example if a document has had fields added, and then deleted, an API client checking for changes will not necessarily receive the intermediate state of added documents.\n\nThis can be used to listen for update and modifications to the database for post processing or synchronization, and for practical purposes, a continuously connected _changes feed is a reasonable approach for generating a real-time log for most applications."
